we can write for loop in 3 different ways
1. list style
for file in app.log nginx.log

2. command style
for pod in $(kubectl get pods -o name)

3. Range style
for i in {1..5}

Below are the -flags which we can use in for conditions.
-z empty
-n not empty
-f file
-d dir

sting logic(=,>,<,=!) and numeric logic(-gt, -ge, -eq, lt)
if you want to do same job on different resources we can use for loop
FOR loop means: "ek ek item uthao aur same kaam karo"

type of loops:
for loop = same work multiple items/list pe karo
while loop = jab tak condition true hai run karo
until loop = jab tak condition false hai run karo

there are 3 ways to use those loops in a format.
1. [condition]
example:
count=1

while [ $count -le 5 ]
do
   echo $count
   count=$((count+1))
done

2. command
example:
while ! systemctl is-active nginx > /dev/null 2>&1
do
   echo "waiting..."
   sleep 5
done

3. infinite loop true
example:
while true
do
   date
   sleep 2
done


echo "===== SYSTEM CHECK END ====="
